comments:
I think the TypeError of type 'circle' is caused by unregistered type name 'circle' in stdLib: https://github.com/antvis/G6/blob/dcb82900dba28f83532fa3ee39727970afdeaf67/packages/g6/src/stdlib/index.ts#L59

Since 'circle' is renamed to 'circle-node' in v5 to avoid the ambiguity of circle shape and circle type node.

If user want to custom a new node type, maybe named 'circle, 'xx-circle', or any string else, register it to the lib like: https://github.com/antvis/G6/blob/dcb82900dba28f83532fa3ee39727970afdeaf67/packages/g6/tests/unit/node-spec.ts#L312

If you want to add built-in type of node, maybe 'rect-node', register it to the stdLib as 'circle-node': https://github.com/antvis/G6/blob/dcb82900dba28f83532fa3ee39727970afdeaf67/packages/g6/src/stdlib/index.ts#L59


P.S. We only plan to add 'circle-node', 'sphere-node'(for 3d), 'rect-node' as built-in node types, they will be registered in G6's source code like the first link above. And other node types which are built-in in v4, e.g. 'star-node', 'triangle-node', etc. will also be implemented as ['circle-node' class here](https://github.com/antvis/G6/blob/v5/packages/g6/src/stdlib/item/node/circle.ts), but won't be registered to stdLib by default as the first link. When user want to use the 'star-node', they need to register it manually before using:

```
// importing the StarNode class from g6, which is not registered but has been defined in official code
import { StarNode } from '@antv/g6';

// register it manually before using
const ExtendedGraph = extend(G6.Graph, {
      nodes: {
        'star-node': StarNode,
      },
});

const graph = new ExtendedGraph({
  node: {
    // star-node can be configured only if it is registered before. 'circle-node' will take effect otherwise as default value
    type: 'star-node', 
  }
})
```


This is quiet different from v4, and this will bring tree-shaking effect.

